SSRPSingle responsibility principle: a class should have only a single responsibility (i.e. only one potential change in the software's specification should be able to affect the specification of the class)MY STUFF HERE
OOCPOpen/closed principle: software entities should be open for extension, but closed for modification.MY STUFF HERE
LLSPLiskov substitution principle: objects in a program should be replaceable with instances of their subtypes without altering the correctness of that program. See also design by contract.MY STUFF HERE
IISPInterface segregation principle: many client-specific interfaces are better than one general-purpose interface.MY STUFF HERE
DDIPDependency inversion principle: one should Depend upon Abstractions. Do not depend upon concretions. Dependency injection is one method of following this principle.MY STUFF HERE
